<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#dcdeed><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucaesiumshadowblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caesium Shadowblade</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>The Grouch</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>posts: </FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>23</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/21/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>9:29:41 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/05/1508005.gif?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Resses, Charging, Donating, and the like</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ok, I'm not a cleric but here's my spin on this. I hope you can relate.<br>
<br>
Personally, I wouldn't look highly upon people charging for rezzes or for doing CR. I guess if you accepted donations then that's fine though if you state &quot;accepting donations for _______ &quot; then let's face it - you want to be paid.<br>
<br>
As it relates to porting I do think it is a different situation. Someone charging for ports does so because they allocate a specific block of playing time to do just that (as in someone only doing ports over a few hours to earn money). Thus, they are compensated in a different manner. I guess if you as a cleric wanted to set up shop like a teleporter and offer rezzes only for a whole zone of people, then it's your right to charge. However, I feel that this does not apply to the everyday situation.<br>
<br>
As a Rogue, I compare my doing CR to a Cleric doing a rez. I have never charged for a CR and when given payment I decline it. Look at it this way: What takes more time, memming and casting a spell, or sneak / hiding yourself to some remote part of a dungeon and dragging that (or those) corpses back to a safe spot for a rez? Not to mention CR puts yourself at a much greater risk than someone sitting at a safe point medding for a rez. How many clerics do you know that have died doing a rez (no, trains to zone-in and mod rod deaths don't count!!)? Rogues unfortunately die quite often trying to get to or from a corpse. No, we dont burn blue juice, but damn if we don't burn the more costly yellow!<br>
<br>
Most Necros charge because there is a physical cost involved with the CR. Yet, in the 2+ years of EQ I have yet to hear a rogue uttering the phrase &quot;Dragging corpses for ____ PP each.&quot; - I just find it interesting that a class that would take less risk and time could justify doing otherwise. The way I look at it, part of a rogues existance is to do CR.<br>
<br>
That's just my take on it - to each his own.</font><P>- Caesium<br>
Rogue of Zebuxoruk<br>
Admin, Rogue's Hideout<br> http://pub41.ezboard.com/bthecrossroadstavern8833<br>
